'''''Norse Mythology''''' is a 2017 book by [[Neil Gaiman]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lifestyle.inquirer.net/257095/thor-odin-story-retold-neil-gaiman-style/|title=Thor and Odin story retold  by Neil Gaiman with style|first=Ruel S. De|last=Vera|publisher=|accessdate=10 May 2018}}</ref> The book is Gaiman's retelling<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2017/feb/12/norse-mythology-neil-gaiman-review-bloomsbury|title=Norse Mythology by Neil Gaiman review – a rich retelling|first=Natalie|last=Haynes|date=12 February 2017|website=the Guardian|accessdate=10 May 2018}}</ref><ref name="ft.com">{{cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/42fad176-ec96-11e6-ba01-119a44939bb6|title=Norse Mythology by Neil Gaiman — northern delights|website=Financial Times|accessdate=10 May 2018}}</ref> of several stories from [[Norse mythology]]. These stories include [[Þrymskviða|the theft of Thor's hammer]], the binding of [[Fenrir]] and other tales about the [[Aesir]].<ref name="ft.com"/><ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/books/neil-gaimans-suspenseful-and-surprising-norse-mythology/2017/02/13/986c0ffe-eef2-11e6-9973-c5efb7ccfb0d_story.html|title=Review - Neil Gaiman’s suspenseful and surprising ‘Norse Mythology’|first=Michael|last=Dirda|date=14 February 2017|publisher=|accessdate=10 May 2018|via=www.washingtonpost.com}}</ref>

The book received positive reviews in ''[[The New Yorker]],''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newyorker.com/books/page-turner/neil-gaiman-reanimates-the-norse-mythsand-loki-once-again-is-the-most-alluring-character|title=Neil Gaiman Reanimates the Norse Myths—and Loki, Once Again, Is the Most Alluring Character|first=Katy|last=Waldman|date=19 March 2018|publisher=|accessdate=10 May 2018|via=www.newyorker.com}}</ref> ''[[Washington Post]]''<ref name="auto"/> and ''[[The Times]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/norse-mythology-by-neil-gaiman-cz8tj3h0p|title=Norse Mythology by Neil Gaiman|first=Laura|last=Freeman|date=10 May 2018|publisher=|accessdate=10 May 2018|via=www.thetimes.co.uk}}</ref> ''[[Kirkus Reviews]]'' called it "Superb. Just the thing for the literate fantasy lover and the student of comparative religion and mythology alike."<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/neil-gaiman/norse-mythology/ |title=''Norse Mythology'' by Neil Gaiman |date=December 1, 2016 |journal=[[Kirkus Reviews]]}}</ref>

